              <note type="proofreader-note">N.B., folio location may not be available for some items below.</note>
              <note type="proofreader-note">N.B., items below may have been listed out of folio order in Wright's catalogue.</note>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                  <p>Greek vowels being occasionally added by a later hand (<foreign xml:lang="syr">ܰ, ܶ, ܺ, ܳ, ܽ andܳ ,</foreign>e.g. foll. <locus from="100a" to="100a">100 a</locus> and <locus from="101a" to="101a">101 a</locus>).</p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition2" n="2">
                  <locus from="25b" to="26"/>
                  <p>The points rukkākh and kushshāi occur on foll. 25 b and 26.</p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition3" n="3">
                  <locus from="129" to="129"/>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">
                      <sic>ܕܠܗ ܫܘܒܚܐ ܠܥܠܡ ܥܠܡܝܢ ܐܡܝܢ. ܐܠܗܐ ܢܚܣܐ ܠܟܠ ܕܫܬܘܬܦ ܐܡܝܢ</sic>.</quote>
                  </p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition4" n="4">
                  <p>Some lessons have been noted on the margins by later hands.</p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition5" n="5">
                  <locus from="1a" to="1a"/>
                  <p>On fol. 1 a the Lord's Prayer is written in an ancient Arabic hand, now much effaced.</p>
